  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> sushi rice </strong>in a sieve under cold running water for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p><p>Add the <strong>drained rice</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Tip: Don't let the water fully boil as this will make the rice stick to the pot!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1628679761036-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1628679761036-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1628679761036-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1628679761036-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1628679761036-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min</p><p>After 15 min, remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for a further 10 min before serving</p><p>Tip: Don't peek! Keep the lid on the whole time to get fluffy and sticky rice!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1628679773508-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1628679773508-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1628679773508-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1628679773508-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1628679773508-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, cut your <strong>cauliflower</strong> into small florets and add to a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and your<strong> soy sauce</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up so the cauliflower is fully coated</p><p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong> to a separate bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>cauliflower</strong> to the bowl of cornflour and give it a good mix up until all the cauliflower is fully coated</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1628679783877-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1628679783877-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1628679783877-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1628679783877-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1628679783877-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to cover the whole base of the pan) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once the pan is very hot, add the <strong>coated cauliflower </strong>and cook for 5-6 min on each side until golden and crispy – this is your <strong>crispy cauliflower</strong></p><p>Tip: You might need to do this in batches!</p><p>Once crispy, transfer to<strong> </strong>kitchen paper<strong> </strong>and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1628679801903-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1628679801903-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1628679801903-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1628679801903-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1628679801903-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the cauliflower is cooking, combine your <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>tomato ketchup</strong>, <strong>honey</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>in a bowl<strong> </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>yang-nyum sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1628679823959-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1628679823959-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1628679823959-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1628679823959-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1628679823959-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and shred and peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Combine 1/2 tsp per person of the <strong>yang-nyum sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) with your <strong>mayo</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> in a separate bowl – this is your <strong>creamy Korean-style dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1628679839504-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1628679839504-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1628679839504-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1628679839504-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1628679839504-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the cauliflower is done, carefully pour away the oil</p><p>Tip: Store it in a glass jar and you can use this oil again for frying!</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat, then once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>yang-nyum sauce</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until thickened</p><p>Once thickened, add the<strong> crispy cauliflower </strong>with your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame</strong> <strong>seeds </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>Korean-style yang-nyum fried cauliflower</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1628679846962-x200.jpg",
